caption: Fig. 1: Empirical evaluations on the CAIDA dataset, comparing flip number of the p-th frequency moment and the residual, for ε = a = 0.001 and p = 1.5 when not variable. Smaller flip numbers indicate less space needed by the algorithm.
description: The figure shows the results of empirical evaluations performed on the CAIDA dataset to compare the flip numbers of the p-th frequency moment and the residual. The results are shown across different accuracy parameters (ε), heavy-hitter parameters (a), and frequency moment parameters (p). Smaller flip numbers suggest that less space is required by the algorithm.
